[3] Argentina
Date: Mon 18 May 2009
Source: Chaco dia por dia [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.chacodiapordia.com/2008/noticia.php?n=29744



The situation room of the NEA [northeastern
Argentina] reported that as of today [18 May
2009], there are 10 379 confirmed individuals ill
with dengue since the beginning of the epidemic,
with 16 reported this Friday [15 May 2009] in the
province and 2193 [cases] under study. They
reported that the great majority of the reported
cases since the beginning of the epidemic are
resolved, regaining their health and without
[further] possibility of transmission of the disease [virus].

"The reports are declining in an accelerated way.
From 170 cases a week ago, we [now] have 30
cases as of yesterday [17 May 2009], " the
Minister of Health, Francisco Baquero, confirmed
in the meeting of the provincial Crisis Committee
for influenza H1N1. Along these lines, and as a
consequence of the statements of Governor Jorge
Capitanich, he stated that "the [epidemic] curve
is going down. We are very alert. We continue
with the Committee functioning very well, and we
are working to install a vector control program,
" the provincial official concluded.

--
