[5] Sri Lanka
Date: Wed 13 May 2009
Source: Daily News Sri Lanka [edited]
<http://www.dailynews.lk/2009/05/13/news13.asp>


So far, 8 suspected dengue patients have died in
the Hambantota district following the spread of
the disease, which originated in Tangalle
recently. Among them were 6 from Tangalle and one
each from Puhulyaya and Wadigala. Altogether, 130
suspected cases have been reported from the
Hambantota district from 1 Apr-10 May [2009]. Of
them, 70 were from Tangalle, 15 from Walasmulla,
40 from Beliatta and 5 from Weeraketiya.

They are receiving treatment at the Matara and Karapitiya hospitals.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Brent Barrett

