[6] Viet Nam (Ho Chi Minh City)
Date: Wed 13 May 2009
Source: Sai Gon Giai Phong (SGGP) Daily [edited]
<http://www.saigon-gpdaily.com.vn/Health/2009/5/70747/>


Three Ho Chi Minh City [HCMC] residents,
including a child, have recently died from dengue fever.

In recent weeks, there has been an outbreak of
dengue fever, with the number of new reported
cases between 145 and 165 a week, the HCM City
Preventive Health Department said [12 May 2009].

Since the beginning of the year [2009], HCM has
recorded nearly 4000 cases, a year-on-year increase of 19 percent.

The disease has taken the lives of 3 patients,
including a child, who were residents of districts 3, Tan Phu, and Binh Tan.

Binh Tan has the highest recorded number of cases
in the city at 297, Thu Duc 2nd with 283 cases,
District 8 (281 cases), Tan Phu (211 cases), and District 6 with 209 cases.

The city's Department of Health has instructed
relevant authorities to carry out necessary
measures to help eliminate the outbreak by the end of May [2009].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-MBDS Rapporteur Vern Weitzel

[Since this is the monsoon season, an outbreak of
dengue infection is ongoing in Viet Nam, with
recent reports of more than 13 000 cases and 11
fatalities from southern provinces (see prior
PRO/MBDS posting Dengue - Viet Nam (05)
20090510.1736). There has been an increase in
admission of dengue patients to hospitals in Ho
Chi Minh City since February 2009 due to
unseasonable rains (see prior PRO/MBDS posting
Dengue - Viet Nam (04): Ho Chi Minh City 20090416.1443).

For maps of Viet Nam with provinces, see
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/vietnam_admin01.jpg> and
<http://www.angelfire.com/co/hongnam/vnmap.html>.
