[7] Saudi Arabia
Date: Tue 12 May 2009
Source: Maktoob.com [edited]
<http://business.maktoob.com/20090000002941/Saudi_sees_outbreak_of_dengue_fever/Article.htm>


Swine flu might have taken the world by storm,
but Saudi health officials say they have treated
72 people for the potentially lethal
mosquito-borne tropical dengue fever in the past
week [week of 3 May 2009]. The patients were
treated in Jeddah, Saudi daily Arab News reported
on Tuesday [12 May 2009]. The newspaper did not
say what condition the patients were in.

